data.meta_description:
164 likes, 2 comments - soho_blues on May 3, 2024: "James Brown, The Godfather of Soul, was born on May 3, 1933, in Barnwell, South Carolina, to a 16-year-old mother named Susie. I've been a fan of his music since I first heard it in the 1950s, and I was privileged to have seen him perform and take portrait photographs in 1979. My shot of James jumping on Broadway has become a rock photo icon. What could be cooler than to hang with Soul Brother Number One? Make it funky, Brother James! Photograph ©1979-2024 Allan Tannenbaum / sohoblues.com all rights reserved. Fine art prints available - link in bio.
